Text.Value: Back to the Hells with what we agreed! I have you now, Raphael. Pay the debt, and I will make this quick.
It's wrong - even a beast like that shouldn't be treated in such a way.
I think 'free' might be rather overstating matters, Yurgir. Devil's in the details, you see, and the details are in the fine print.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Raphael magically appears. The orthon snarls and aims his bow at the cambion
EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support - Raphael magical appearance + Foley - Raising Crossbow.

Text.Value: You're lucky I came along to help. Now you owe me.
The song remains. Seems you haven't dealt with this imaginary justiciar of yours.
Only what I can smell. And whatever engine burns within you is grinding to an inevitable explosion. Burning and fear - you reek with it.
Few may walk away from you intact, Yurgir, but none walk away from me in violation of their deal.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Raphael magically appears. The orthon snarls and aims his bow at the cambion
EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support - Raphael magical appearance + Foley - Raising Crossbow.

Text.Value: Clever. I'd like to try that for myself.
I know what you're feeding that displacer charm potions. Curious way of ensuring the beast's loyalty.
You'd imagine wrong. Nessa is as loyal as can be.
*You feel a telltale ache coming from the wound in your hand. Pain will soon grip you - for what you have done.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: SH concerned expression, anticipating wound flare-up post scene. CFR river stas

Text.Value: What...? You think you can flaunt my prize - my freedom - under my nose, then deny it?

EditorData.NodeContext: Slow realisation of what the player is telling him, before flying into a fury.

Text.Value: Unless, of course, you consider instead my infinite mercy. A new contract. A chance to balance the books. Not to mention a welcome change of scenery.
But now the song has stopped - the contract is fulfilled. I suppose you showing up at the same time is no coincidence...
Any suggestions on where to look?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Local flag unsets when the player acknowledges the Orthon's query in N200

Text.Value: I am a Dark Justiciar now. That makes you my enemy.
So you charm the displacer yourself?
You'd better start taking this hunt more seriously, or you'll wish you were a bloody rat!
Consider your position. You are about to forfeit what reputation you have left. No contracts. No fame. No power. You'll be a streak of excrement even lemures will slither away from.
Treated like what? Pampered? Fed? Given a master to adore?
You've got the stench of the Hells about you - the stench of home. And a whiff of the surface besides.
Just getting my bearings. This place is confounding.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Local flag unsets when the player acknowledges the Orthon's query in N200

Text.Value: Those who live to speak my name call me Yurgir.
Give it a decade, or ten - then you'll know it like the back of your hand.
What do you know of infernal machinery?
You - tiefling. You've got the stench of the Hells about you - the stench of home. And a whiff of the surface besides.
Hardly - I already found a necromancer, Balthazar, elsewhere in the temple. Perhaps he's the one you need to kill.
But go on - spill some blood prove me wrong. If there truly is a justiciar, the song will end and you will be vindicated.
It seems you're free to go.
I'm done with Zariel. Dealt with enough devils to last a lifetime.
Those potions you use on the displacer - where might I get some of those?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This node if the player already asked about the displacer being charmed, but hadn't asked to try the potions for themselves.

Text.Value: No point, really. Forget it.
No. You're here to solve my problem. I suggest you prove yourself useful.
Ensuring Nessa's loyalty is as important as having sharpened blades and an oiled crossbow.
I caught the scent of that bloated carcass already - he's no more alive than the Dark Justiciars down here.
Now leave me. I must prepare for my return to Hell - triumphant.
Wait... quiet...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Palm of one hand raised in a 'hold on' gesture. Head cocked, listening.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This greeting if the Last Justiciar contract has been completed by the player
EditorData.NodeContext: Glimmer of hope. Hushing the player, listening intently.
EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] Sound of silence, there is no more music playing for the Orthon - The calm.

Text.Value: So you're telling me you completed the rites? Congratulations, little rabbit. I suppose I'd better kill you now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Utters a chuckle before speaking with vicious amusement - player has signed their death warrant in his eyes.

Text.Value: And a short one it will be, by the smell of that engine. What will it be - hours? Days? Finish your search before we both run out of time.
Just admiring your enterprise. I'd like to try it out for myself.
You what? No new darkcloaks have been sworn in for years here - not since I arrived.
An orthon. Fancy seeing one of you so far from the Hells.
What's a contract without whimsy, I say, but fine: no more songs. Now off to the House of Hope for cocktails and canaps - and a brand new signature on a brand new deal.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Raphael, the Orthon, and all his remaining retinue (displacer and merregons) poof away.
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Every characters except the player and companions magically poof away.

Text.Value: What's the point in having lackeys if I've to do everything myself? The quartermaster makes sure the displacer's meals are properly seasoned.
I'm not here to talk about Zariel.
See my quartermaster. It may have some spare potions to sell you - let you experiment for yourself.
Do not provoke her. I am her master - all others are a potential meal.
You're supposed to be searching these ruins, little rabbit. Given up already?
...It's gone. The song is gone! The contract is completed!

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] Sound of silence, there is no more music playing for the Orthon - The calm.

Text.Value: He is not the answer. He is not my prey.
Now answer my question - are you still searching this place, or have you failed already?
I found your quarry. But I will not harm him - nor will you.
Holy shit. An orthon. Powerful devils - I wouldn't get on their bad side without a good reason.
An impressive companion, your displacer. But a handful, I'd imagine.

EditorData.logicalname: DOESN'T KNOW ABOUT DISPLACER CHARMED MEAT

Text.Value: Here I am, Yurgir, tongue and all, precisely on time for a lesson in semantics.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Raphael magically appears. The orthon snarls and aims his bow at the cambion
EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support - Raphael magical appearance + Foley - Raising Crossbow.

Text.Value: You've got the stench of the Hells about you - the stench of home. And a whiff of the surface besides.
Who the Hells are you?
Devil's in the details, you see, and the details are in the fine print.
Thought I smelled the stench of Avernus.
Yes. Your point?
You - tiefling. You've got the stench of the Hells about you - the stench of home. And a whiff of the surface besides.
Anything I leave behind is yours. Pick over it however you like.

EditorData.AnimationTags: TBD - If the reward is small (fits in 1 hand - use construction animation) <Amelie>

Text.Value: Only what I can smell. And whatever engine burns within you is grinding to an inevitable explosion. Burning and fear - it's all over you.
Can we please kill it this time?
I suggest you think twice before pestering me, or our truce may end prematurely.
The rats? Why would I pay attention to some puny vermin?
I still hear the song, which means you've achieved nothing. Keep looking, or I'll decorate every corner of this place with pieces of you.

EditorData.logicalname: Agreed to Search Temple - Backup Hasmet

Text.Value: Though in truth, you won't have that long. Not even close.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wicked, predatory. Anticipating the player's failure.

Text.Value: Attack.
I will take care of him. After I've shown you your own heart.
There was one last justiciar - dead now. Raphael helped him hide from you.
A servant of Zariel, if I'm not mistaken. I'd know the reek of her infernal machinery anywhere.
Suggestions? So much for your superior hunting skills.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mocking incredulity at the player asking for tips.

Text.Value: But first, it would be only befitting if you reward your subcontractor. The greater reward for the greater hunter.
I was bid by Raphael to slay every justiciar I found in this place. The contract was a song, one stuck in my head until I finished the deed. I had to hum that blasted tune for years.
Leave.
That conniving sack of worms. I should've known. I've should've ripped his tongue out before he even spoke of this contract.
What do you know of infernal machinery?

EditorData.NodeContext: To the orthon. Adversarial, but she's hoping he knows something useful.

Text.Value: I met a necromancer, Balthazar, elsewhere in the temple. Perhaps he's the one you need to kill.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Alt question for cases where SHA_Orthon_Event_OrthonQuestionsSearch has already been set before the topic of Balthazar is raised

Text.Value: Remember you said that, when you fail. You won't smile so easily when I peel the face off your skull.

EditorData.NodeContext: Vicious. Chaffing at the player's bravado.

Text.Value: ...Bastard. Fine. On one condition - no more songs.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Long, hateful scowl from the Orthon, before he finally relents, lowers his crossbow and answers.

Text.Value: In short: you're in breach of contract, my friend. Oh dear.
Don't insult me - I'd know if there was a justiciar down there.
Away now. There is nothing more for you here, unless you're offering yourself as hunting practice.
This is what Raphael wants us to kill? Well, if that's what it takes to figure out what these damn scars mean...

EditorData.NodeContext: Not looking forward to this fight - you're up against a big boi

Text.Value: You're wasting time, little rabbit. Hoping I'll show mercy instead?
For a moment, I thought you were going to challenge me. Wise, that you didn't.
Holy shit. An orthon. Powerful devils - I wouldn't get on their bad side without a good reason.
What do you know of infernal machinery?

EditorData.NodeContext: To the orthon. Adversarial, but she's hoping he knows something useful.

Text.Value: Spare me your bleeding heart. Unless you'd like me to pluck it out and show it to you.
You're manipulating that creature.
Only what I can smell. And whatever engine burns within you is grinding to an inevitable explosion. Burning and fear - you reek with it.
A servant of Zariel, if I'm not mistaken. I'd know the reek of her infernal machinery anywhere.
Song? Contract? What are you talking about?
Yes - I'd recognise it anywhere. Zariel. The oily reek of her infernal machinery.
I found one last justiciar, hiding in plain sight. He's in a chamber right below you.
You were to fulfil the deal. Nowhere does it stipulate you could subcontract the last kill to the first adventurers' party that came trotting along.
Curious? No - effective. A hunter needs to ensure his tools are dependable.
Not at all. I think I'll make short work of this - show you how it's done.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Local flag unsets when the player acknowledges the Orthon's query in N200

Text.Value: Have you noticed anything strange about the rats around here?
Owe you? Every breath you take from this moment on is my reward to you. Few walk away from me intact.

Synopsis:
This occurs if the player has successfully convinced the orthon to let them stay in his lair. They did so by telling him they'd search the temple for a way of freeing him from his contract.
If the player resolves the Last Justiciar contract, they can inform Yurgir. If they killed the justiciar, Raphael will appear and negotiate with Yurgir. If the player spared the justiciar, they can confront and fight Yurgir.
